Yes, here's how to structure it:

---

## Option A: Dedicated Repo (Recommended for Paper)

```bash
# Create the repo
mkdir carry-strategy-research
cd carry-strategy-research
git init

# Create structure
mkdir -p .claude/skills/{carry-execution,preregistration-validator,bond-data-profiler,data-availability-checker}
mkdir -p .claude/commands
mkdir -p research/preregistration
mkdir -p data/{reference,pricing,trace}
mkdir -p src/{strategies,backtest,data}
mkdir -p reports
mkdir -p docs

# Create placeholder files
touch CLAUDE.md
touch .gitignore
```

### .gitignore

```gitignore
# Data (too large for git)
data/pricing/*.parquet
data/trace/*.parquet
data/reference/*.parquet

# Keep structure
!data/*/.gitkeep

# Python
__pycache__/
*.pyc
.venv/
venv/

# IDE
.vscode/
.idea/

# Reports (optional - may want to track)
# reports/*.csv

# Secrets
.env
*.key
```

