## Option B: Monorepo (If You Have Multiple Strategies)

```
optiver-research/                      # Or whatever umbrella name
├── CLAUDE.md                          # Global conventions
├── .claude/
│   ├── skills/                        # Shared skills
│   │   ├── bond-data-profiler/
│   │   └── preregistration-validator/
│   └── commands/
├── strategies/
│   ├── carry/                         # This project
│   │   ├── CLAUDE.md                  # Strategy-specific overrides
│   │   ├── .claude/
│   │   │   └── skills/
│   │   │       └── carry-execution/
│   │   ├── research/
│   │   ├── src/
│   │   └── reports/
│   ├── value/
│   │   └── ...
│   └── momentum/
│       └── ...
├── data/                              # Shared data
└── libs/                              # Shared code
    └── backtest/
```

---

## Quick Setup Script

```bash
#!/bin/bash
# setup-carry-repo.sh

REPO_NAME="carry-strategy-research"

mkdir -p $REPO_NAME
cd $REPO_NAME
git init

# Directories
mkdir -p .claude/skills/{carry-execution,preregistration-validator,bond-data-profiler,data-availability-checker}
mkdir -p .claude/commands
mkdir -p research/{preregistration,hypotheses}
mkdir -p docs
mkdir -p data/{reference,pricing,trace}
mkdir -p src/{strategies,backtest,data}
mkdir -p reports
mkdir -p tests

# Placeholders
touch data/{reference,pricing,trace}/.gitkeep
touch reports/.gitkeep

# .gitignore
cat > .gitignore << 'EOF'
data/**/*.parquet
data/**/*.csv
!data/**/.gitkeep
__pycache__/
*.pyc
.venv/
.env
.vscode/
.idea/
EOF

# Empty CLAUDE.md
touch CLAUDE.md

echo "Repo created. Run 'claude' to start populating files."
```

Run it:

```bash
chmod +x setup-carry-repo.sh
./setup-carry-repo.sh
cd carry-strategy-research
claude
```

---

## Then in Claude Code

```
> Create CLAUDE.md for a credit carry strategy research project.
> Include: code standards, research discipline (pre-registration, holdout, kill criteria), 
> file paths, available skills, anti-patterns.

> Create the carry-execution skill from my pre-registration framework.

> Create the preregistration-validator skill.

> Create the bond-data-profiler and data-availability-checker skills.

> Create slash commands for run-carry, validate-prereg, profile-data, check-data.
```

---

## Commit Workflow

```bash
# Initial commit
git add .
git commit -m "Initial repo setup with Claude Code configuration"

# After creating skills
git add .claude/
git commit -m "Add skills: carry-execution, preregistration-validator, data profiling"

# Freeze pre-registration (IMPORTANT: tag it)
git add research/preregistration/carry_structural_v0.yaml
git commit -m "Freeze pre-registration spec v0"
git tag -a prereg-v0 -m "Pre-registration frozen - DO NOT MODIFY"
```

The git tag creates an immutable reference point — critical for your audit trail.

---

## TL;DR

**Yes, create a dedicated repo called `carry-strategy-research`** (or similar). Put everything inside it:

```bash
mkdir carry-strategy-research && cd carry-strategy-research
git init
# ... create structure ...
claude
```

This keeps the paper, code, pre-registration, and Claude Code config together as one auditable unit.
